I do not know English perfectly, nor am I familiar with your dialect, but this dialogue of the deaf is solely due to your own analphabetically unlettered illiteracy; communication is a two-way street.

: Our cultural differences are not to blame.
: Your uncultured interpretation is untame.
: I am right, and your are wrong.
